  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      By this study the investigators wish to (1) quantify hip strength and functional-performance
      deficits at discharge after fast-track total hip arthroplasty (THA), and (2) investigate if
      changes in thigh circumferences, or hip pain are correlated to changes in hip strength and
      functional-performance after fast-track THA.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The investigators intend to use the results to optimize the rehabilitation programs for THA
      patients shortly after surgery
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
